examples.en: He had a book clutched in his hand.
She clutched my arm when she got scared
He clutched at a pillar for support.
He clutched the flowers to his bosom.
He clutched a jag of the rock.
The child clutched at his mother in fear.
The child clutched her mother's hand firmly.
She gave a little gasp and clutched George's hand.
The climber clutched at the swinging rope, but missed.
Helen clutched Edward's arm as they dodged through the traffic.
The child clutched the doll to her and would not show it to anyone.
The man clutched his heavy frock as he made his way through the driving rain.
